FuncDef: The cut access-user cgn-pub-user command logs out CGN public network users and switches public IP address-based access back to private IP address-based access.

ParaDef.Info:
Indicates DHCP CGN public network users.
-

Indicates non-DHCP CGN public network users.
-

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
You can run the cut access-user cgn-pub-user command to log out CGN public network users and switch public IP address-based access back to private IP address-based access after a faulty service board recovers.
Precautions
A CGN device undergoes the internal logout process for CGN users cutback, which cannot trigger logout for DHCP CGN public network users. Therefore, the CGN device differentiates the DHCP CGN public network users and the other users.
This command only takes effect on VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
